  <bioghist id="aspace_67d7c9299ef44f4c2f15701dc813bb0c">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Frank Monaghan (Cornell University Class of 1927, M.S. 1928) was a Professor of History at New York University.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_0a94ddba56383c6771e8c62d736c7433">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Pamphlets, notes, and correspondence concerning World's Fairs and Expositions, ca.1894-1968; correspondence and pamphlets concerning Cornell University, ca.1931-1968; pamphlets, correspondence, notes, news clippings, typescripts of books, and a list of illustrations for a book; and five plaques of Frank Monaghan.</p><p> A large portion of the material is in French.</p>  </scopecontent>
